OCTAVIUS

For information concerning Ianuarius Octavius we are altogether dependent on the Dialogue. Possibly he also hailed from Africa, where he probably lived with his wife and family at the period of his visit to Rome.⁴ He had probably died before the date of production of the work which bears his name.5 He had been on most intimate terms of friendship with Minucius from his earliest youth,6 having preceded him into the Christian fold,7 where he was evidently a man of prominence.8 He is the champion of Christianity in the Dialogue.
